Class CampSiteStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • CampSiteStore
  • public class CampSiteStore
extends java.lang.Object
    The data structure for storing off CampSites. Underlying data structure is a TreeSet. A TreeSet is chosen because we want to sort the CampSites (by id), but we do not want duplicates.
    Author:
    Paul Salmon

      • getInstance

        public static CampSiteStore getInstance()
        Singleton instance getter. There should rightfully be only one store for CampSites, so a Singleton was used. Singleton is initialized in the handler because we use reflections to deal with testing our static types.
        Returns:
        the singleton CampSiteStore instance.

      • getNameById

        public java.lang.String getNameById​(int id)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        string of the campsites NAME.

      • addCampsite

        public boolean addCampsite​(CampSite campSite)
        Adds the new CampSite to our underlying TreeSet if it has a unique ID.
        Parameters:
        campSite - the CampSite that we are trying to add, but will check the ID to see if it already exists in our store.
        Returns:
        true if we can add, false if not (because the ID exists).
